<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Always check the function attribute to determine checksum mismatch for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &#96;available&#95;externally&#96; functions even if their desc are available. This</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// is because the desc is computed based on the original internal function</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// and it&#39;s substituted by the &#96;available&#95;externally&#96; function during link</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// time. However, when unstable IR or ODR violation issue occurs, the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// definitions of the same function across different translation units could</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// be different and result in different checksums. So we should use the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// state from the new (available&#95;externally) function, which is saved in its</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00140" /><CodeLine lineNumber="140"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// attribute.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00141" /><CodeLine lineNumber="141"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// TODO: If the function&#39;s profile only exists as nested inlinee profile in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00142" /><CodeLine lineNumber="142"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// a different module, we don&#39;t have the attr mismatch state(unknown), we</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00143" /><CodeLine lineNumber="143"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// need to fix it later.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Find equivalence classes for the given block.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This finds all the blocks that are guaranteed to execute the same</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><Highlight kind="comment">/// number of times as \\p BB1. To do this, it traverses all the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><Highlight kind="comment">/// descendants of \\p BB1 in the dominator or post-dominator tree.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A block BB2 will be in the same equivalence class as \\p BB1 if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the following holds:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1- \\p BB1 is a descendant of BB2 in the opposite tree. So, if BB2</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment">///    is a descendant of \\p BB1 in the dominator tree, then BB2 should</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment">///    dominate BB1 in the post-dominator tree.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2- Both BB2 and \\p BB1 must be in the same loop.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For every block BB2 that meets those two requirements, we set BB2&#39;s</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment">/// equivalence class to \\p BB1.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param BB1  Block to check.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param Descendants  Descendants of \\p BB1 in either the dom or pdom tree.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param DomTree  Opposite dominator tree. If \\p Descendants is filled</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment">///                 with blocks from \\p BB1&#39;s dominator tree, then</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="comment">///                 this is the post-dominator tree, and vice versa.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Find equivalence classes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Since samples may be missing from blocks, we can fill in the gaps by setting</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// All the basic blocks in the same equivalence class will execute</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Visit all the predecessor and successor edges to determine</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> i = 0; i &lt; 2; i++) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><Highlight kind="normal">      uint64&#95;t TotalWeight = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumUnknownEdges = 0, NumTotalEdges = 0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ae0c6798ea9e2df9241569f6b9f6287da">Edge</a> UnknownEdge, SelfReferentialEdge, SingleEdge;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (i == 0) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// First, visit all predecessor edges.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><Highlight kind="normal">        NumTotalEdges = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ab84644c12ae7f1ff1b2db384132d0b4c">Predecessors</a>&#91;BB&#93;.size();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;Pred : <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ab84644c12ae7f1ff1b2db384132d0b4c">Predecessors</a>&#91;BB&#93;) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><Highlight kind="normal">          <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ae0c6798ea9e2df9241569f6b9f6287da">Edge</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a> = std::make&#95;pair(Pred, BB);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="normal">          TotalWeight += <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ab32be71f5ab339400be1f2eba700b290">visitEdge</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a>, &amp;NumUnknownEdges, &amp;UnknownEdge);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="normal">          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a>.first == <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a>.second)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="normal">            SelfReferentialEdge = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#abb2b3a60ccc38a28239e19a1646e0c8a">E</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="normal">        &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (NumTotalEdges == 1) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><Highlight kind="normal">          SingleEdge = std::make&#95;pair(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ab84644c12ae7f1ff1b2db384132d0b4c">Predecessors</a>&#91;BB&#93;&#91;0&#93;, BB);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><Highlight kind="normal">        &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125; </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// On the second round, visit all successor edges.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><Highlight kind="normal">        NumTotalEdges = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ad6a5a5bd663105131550df5f7593ef0f">Successors</a>&#91;BB&#93;.size();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;Succ : <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ad6a5a5bd663105131550df5f7593ef0f">Successors</a>&#91;BB&#93;) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="normal">        &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><Highlight kind="normal">          SingleEdge = std::make&#95;pair(BB, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprofileloaderbaseimpl/#ad6a5a5bd663105131550df5f7593ef0f">Successors</a>&#91;BB&#93;&#91;0&#93;);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><Highlight kind="normal">        &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// After visiting all the edges, there are three cases that we</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// can handle immediately:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - All the edge weights are known (i.e., NumUnknownEdges == 0).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   In this case, we simply check that the sum of all the edges</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   is the same as BB&#39;s weight. If not, we change BB&#39;s weight</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   to match. Additionally, if BB had not been visited before,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   we mark it visited.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - Only one edge is unknown and BB has already been visited.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   In this case, we can compute the weight of the edge by</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   subtracting the total block weight from all the known</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   edge weights. If the edges weight more than BB, then the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00783" /><CodeLine lineNumber="783"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   edge of the last remaining edge is set to zero.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// - There exists a self-referential edge and the weight of BB is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   known. In this case, this edge can be based on BB&#39;s weight.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   We add up all the other known edges and set the weight on</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00788" /><CodeLine lineNumber="788"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   the self-referential edge as we did in the previous case.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00789" /><CodeLine lineNumber="789"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// In any other case, we must continue iterating. Eventually,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00791" /><CodeLine lineNumber="791"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// all edges will get a weight, or iteration will stop when</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00792" /><CodeLine lineNumber="792"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// it reaches SampleProfileMaxPropagateIterations.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00793" /><CodeLine lineNumber="793"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (NumUnknownEdges &lt;= 1) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Propagate weights into edges</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The following rules are applied to every block BB in the CFG:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - If BB has a single predecessor/successor, then the weight</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><Highlight kind="comment">///   of that edge is the weight of the block.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="907"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - If all incoming or outgoing edges are known except one, and the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><Highlight kind="comment">///   weight of the block is already known, the weight of the unknown</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><Highlight kind="comment">///   edge will be the weight of the block minus the sum of all the known</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="910"><Highlight kind="comment">///   edges. If the sum of all the known edges is larger than BB&#39;s weight,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="911"><Highlight kind="comment">///   we set the unknown edge weight to zero.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00912" /><CodeLine lineNumber="912"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><Highlight kind="comment">/// - If there is a self-referential edge, and the weight of the block is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="914"><Highlight kind="comment">///   known, the weight for that edge is set to the weight of the block</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"><Highlight kind="comment">///   minus the weight of the other incoming edges to that block (if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><Highlight kind="comment">///   known).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="917"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> BT&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00979" /><CodeLine lineNumber="979"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00980" /><CodeLine lineNumber="980"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Generate branch weight metadata for all branches in \\p F.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00981" /><CodeLine lineNumber="981"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00982" /><CodeLine lineNumber="982"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Branch weights are computed out of instruction samples using a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00983" /><CodeLine lineNumber="983"><Highlight kind="comment">/// propagation heuristic. Propagation proceeds in 3 phases:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00984" /><CodeLine lineNumber="984"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00985" /><CodeLine lineNumber="985"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1- Assignment of block weights. All the basic blocks in the function</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00986" /><CodeLine lineNumber="986"><Highlight kind="comment">///    are initial assigned the same weight as their most frequently</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00987" /><CodeLine lineNumber="987"><Highlight kind="comment">///    executed instruction.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00988" /><CodeLine lineNumber="988"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00989" /><CodeLine lineNumber="989"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2- Creation of equivalence classes. Since samples may be missing from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00990" /><CodeLine lineNumber="990"><Highlight kind="comment">///    blocks, we can fill in the gaps by setting the weights of all the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00991" /><CodeLine lineNumber="991"><Highlight kind="comment">///    blocks in the same equivalence class to the same weight. To compute</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00992" /><CodeLine lineNumber="992"><Highlight kind="comment">///    the concept of equivalence, we use dominance and loop information.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00993" /><CodeLine lineNumber="993"><Highlight kind="comment">///    Two blocks B1 and B2 are in the same equivalence class if B1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00994" /><CodeLine lineNumber="994"><Highlight kind="comment">///    dominates B2, B2 post-dominates B1 and both are in the same loop.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00995" /><CodeLine lineNumber="995"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00996" /><CodeLine lineNumber="996"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 3- Propagation of block weights into edges. This uses a simple</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00997" /><CodeLine lineNumber="997"><Highlight kind="comment">///    propagation heuristic. The following rules are applied to every</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00998" /><CodeLine lineNumber="998"><Highlight kind="comment">///    block BB in the CFG:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00999" /><CodeLine lineNumber="999"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01000" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1000"><Highlight kind="comment">///    - If BB has a single predecessor/successor, then the weight</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01001" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1001"><Highlight kind="comment">///      of that edge is the weight of the block.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1002"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><Highlight kind="comment">///    - If all the edges are known except one, and the weight of the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><Highlight kind="comment">///      block is already known, the weight of the unknown edge will</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01005" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1005"><Highlight kind="comment">///      be the weight of the block minus the sum of all the known</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1006"><Highlight kind="comment">///      edges. If the sum of all the known edges is larger than BB&#39;s weight,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1007"><Highlight kind="comment">///      we set the unknown edge weight to zero.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><Highlight kind="comment">///    - If there is a self-referential edge, and the weight of the block is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><Highlight kind="comment">///      known, the weight for that edge is set to the weight of the block</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1011"><Highlight kind="comment">///      minus the weight of the other incoming edges to that block (if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1012"><Highlight kind="comment">///      known).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1013"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1014"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Since this propagation is not guaranteed to finalize for every CFG, we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1015"><Highlight kind="comment">/// only allow it to proceed for a limited number of iterations (controlled</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1016"><Highlight kind="comment">/// by -sample-profile-max-propagate-iterations).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1017"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1018"><Highlight kind="comment">/// FIXME: Try to replace this propagation heuristic with a scheme</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1019"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that is guaranteed to finalize. A work-list approach similar to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1020"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the standard value propagation algorithm used by SSA-CCP might</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1021"><Highlight kind="comment">/// work here.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1022"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1023"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\param F The function to query.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1024"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1025"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\returns true if \\p F was modified. Returns false, otherwise.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1026"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">template</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &lt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">typename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> BT&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
